<HEAD>President Arrested, Charged With Inciting Mutiny</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORT VILA, Vanuatu (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Sokomanu </PERSON> was arrested on Wednesday and charged with inciting mutiny in a deepening political crisis in this <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> state, the Australian <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> news agency reported. <PERSON> Sokomanu </PERSON> faces a maximum sentence of life imprisonment, and the agency quoted Public Prosecutor <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Baxter-Wright </PERSON> as saying additional charges would be levied against him. On Tuesday, <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION> acted to remove <PERSON> Sokomanu </PERSON> from office for his failed attempt two days earlier to form an interim government pending national elections in February. Legislators accused him of treason, gross misconduct and other major offenses. <PERSON> Sokomanu </PERSON> tried last Friday to dissolve <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION> and to dismiss elected Prime Minister <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> Lini </PERSON> and replace with <PERSON> Sokomanu </PERSON>'s nephew, flamboyant, Australian-educated politician <PERSON> Barak </PERSON> <PERSON> Sope </PERSON> <PERSON> Lini </PERSON> has been in power since <LOCATION> Vanuatu </LOCATION>, formerly known as the New Hebrides and under Anglo-French rule, became independent in 1980. The <ORGANIZATION> AAP </ORGANIZATION> said the president was charged during a five-minute appearance at <ORGANIZATION> Port </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Vila </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Magistrate </ORGANIZATION>'s Court. It said Senior Magistrate <PERSON> Dawn </PERSON> <PERSON> Barcinski </PERSON> asked the president if he had anything to say, and he replied: `` Your Honor, I would like to see my lawyer first.'' The president, clad in a sport shirt and shorts, waved to spectators as he walked from the court and was led away to a police vehicle, guarded by about 12 uniformed officers, the <ORGANIZATION> AAP </ORGANIZATION> said. Four members of the abortive interim government, including <PERSON> Sope </PERSON>, already have been charged with sedition. All five men are scheduled to apply for bail later Wednesday before the <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>. The crisis culminates a yearlong power struggle between <PERSON> Lini </PERSON> and <PERSON> Sope </PERSON>, whose foes blamed him for recent outbreaks of violence in his bid for leadership. This island nation of 130,000 people lies 1,200 miles northeast of <LOCATION> Brisbane </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>.
