<HEAD>Bank Robber Dies In Siege After Policeman Killed In Raid</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhotos LON3,4,5</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COVENTRY, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Bank robbers killed one policeman and seriously wounded another in the central <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> city of Coventry Monday before holing up in a suburban house where one robber shot himself to death, police said. One of the alleged robbers gave himself up but the other ignored police attempts to negotiate and then shot himself in the head in a back room of the house, said <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Midlands </LOCATION> Assistant Chief Constable <PERSON> Mervyn </PERSON> <PERSON> Jones </PERSON>. Police Superintendent <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Burton </PERSON> said the officer who died was an unarmed patrolman in his mid-30s. He was thought to have died instantly after being shot at point-blank range with a double-barreled shotgun. Police said he had stopped the raiders' getaway car soon after the robbery at the <ORGANIZATION> Midland </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> in which $ 1,100 was stolen. The robbers then switched cars and drove onto a highway where they were rammed by an unmarked police car. Police said a patrolman in that vehicle was shot in the stomach. The gunmen then ran across a golf course before forcing their way into the home of a plumbing contractor and his family. It was not known whether they took any hostages. Police said the wounded officer, also in his 30s, was recovering in hospital. A third officer was being treated in hospital for shock.
