<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Holiday moviegoers are favoring comedy over drama, as the lighthearted `` Twins'' topped the new drama `` Rain Man,'' according to weekend box-office figures. For the second week in a row, `` Twins'' was the nation's most popular movie, and two comedies, `` The Naked Gun'' and `` Scrooged,'' finished ahead of the serious `` Tequila Sunrise.'' According to figures issued Monday by <ORGANIZATION> Exhibitor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Relations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, No. 1 `` Twins,'' focusing on non-identical brothers -LRB- <PERSON> Arnold </PERSON> <PERSON> Schwarzenegger </PERSON> and <PERSON> Danny </PERSON> <PERSON> DeVito </PERSON> -RRB- separated at birth, grossed $ 7.8 million. In second place was `` Rain Man,'' the new drama about an autistic savant -LRB- <PERSON> Dustin </PERSON> <PERSON> Hoffman </PERSON> -RRB- on the road with his conniving brother -LRB- <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Cruise </PERSON> -RRB-. `` Rain Man'' collected $ 7 million. Two other comedies continued strongly, as `` The Naked Gun: From the Files of Police Squad!'' and `` Scrooged'' finished in third and fourth place, respectively. `` The Naked Gun'' a spoof of police movies starring <PERSON> Leslie </PERSON> <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON>, sold $ 5.6 million worth of tickets, while `` Scrooged,'' <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Murray </PERSON>'s comic interpretation of the Dickens classic, gathered $ 4.6 million. In fifth place was the new comedy `` Dirty Rotten Scoundrels,'' starring <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> and <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Caine </PERSON> as dueling con men, opened weakly with receipts of $ 3.8 million. It was followed by `` Tequila Sunrise,'' a drama featuring <PERSON> Mel </PERSON> <PERSON> Gibson </PERSON> as a reformed drug dealer, which drew $ 3 million. The holiday season's two animated films _ `` <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> and Co.'' and `` The Land Before Time'' _ finished in seventh and eighth place. `` <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> and Co.,'' an <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> Twist-inspired story about a homeless kitten, grossed $ 2.3 million. `` The Land Before Time,'' a tale of baby dinosaurs negotiating a perilous prehistoric world, collected $ 1.5 million. Rounding out the Top 10 were the failed `` My Stepmother is an Alien,'' with <PERSON> Kim </PERSON> <PERSON> Basinger </PERSON> as an extraterrestrial beauty, and `` Ernest Saves Christmas,'' with <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Varney </PERSON>. `` My Stepmother,'' dropping to ninth place from seventh a week ago, grossed just $ 1.1 million in its second week of release, while `` Ernest,'' at No. 10, took in $ 950,000. The holiday film season grows even more frantic this week, as studios release their `` prestige'' titles to qualify for the Academy Awards. Movies opening this week, some only in selected cities, include `` Beaches,'' `` Working Girl,'' `` Talk Radio,'' `` The Accidental Tourist,'' `` Hellbound: Hellraiser II,'' `` Burning Secret,'' `` Dangerous Liaisons,'' `` Women on the Verge of a Nervous Breakdown,'' `` The Boost'' and `` Pelle the Conqueror.'' Here are the top movies for the weekend as tallied by Exhibitor Relations, with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater screens, average per screen, total gross and number of weeks in release. 1. `` Twins,'' Universal, $ 7.8 million, 1,449 screens, $ 5,370 per screen, $ 22.1 million, two weeks. 2. `` Rain Man,'' <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Artists </ORGANIZATION>, $ 7 million, 1,248 screens, $ 5,614 per screen, $ 7 million, one week. 3. `` The Naked Gun,'' Paramount, $ 5.6 million, 1,937 screens, $ 2,894 per screen, $ 25.8 million, three weeks. 4. `` Scrooged,'' Paramount, $ 4.6 million, 1,797 screens, $ 2,538 per screen, $ 41.9 million, four weeks. 5. `` Dirty Rotten Scoundrels,'' <ORGANIZATION> Orion </ORGANIZATION>, $ 3.8 million, 1,466 screens, $ 2,592 per screen, $ 3.8 million, one week. 6. `` Tequila Sunrise,'' <