<HEAD>Court Orders New Inquest Into IRA Shootings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>'s highest court today ordered a new inquest into the deaths of three unarmed <ORGANIZATION> Irish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> members shot by police six years ago. The Northern Ireland Court of Appeal ruled that the three police officers who fired the shots can be forced to testify at the new hearing. No date has been set. But Sir <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Hutton </PERSON>, the chief justice, made it clear that the police officers _ who have been acquitted of murdering one of the <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> members _ can refuse to testify on grounds of possible self-incrimination. The original inquest was adjourned in late November. The three members of the <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ulster </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Constabulary </ORGANIZATION>, the province's police force, were among five police officers involved in the ambush on <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> members <PERSON> Gervase </PERSON> <PERSON> McKerr </PERSON>, <PERSON> Eugene </PERSON> <PERSON> Toman </PERSON> and <PERSON> Sean </PERSON> <PERSON> Burns </PERSON>. The three men allegedly failed to stop their car at a police checkpoint in <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Armagh </LOCATION> in November 1982. <PERSON> Eleanor </PERSON> <PERSON> McKerr </PERSON>, the widow of one of the victims, fought to have the courts order the police officers to testify and be cross-examined rather than submit written statements. Coroner <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Elliott </PERSON> had ruled he had no power to compel the police officers to appear in person. However, his original inquest has been scrapped and the jury discharged. Inquests also are to be held into the deaths of three other unarmed Roman Catholics _ two of them guerrillas and the third a teen-age civilian _ who died in two separate police ambushes in 1982. Police said