<SECOND>PM-Wall Street Closing,0185</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A late selling wave left stock prices broadly lower today, as the market ran into resistance in its bid to extend its recent rally. The market appeared to take some early encouragement from a pair of economic reports that seemed to signal low inflation and moderate economic growth. The government reported the consumer price index rose 0.3 percent in November, and lowered its estimate of economic growth in the July-through-September period to 2.5 percent from 2.6 percent. The reports contributed to a rally in the credit markets, where prices of some long-term bonds were up by as much as $ 9 for every $ 1,000 in face value while interest rates pulled back. But analysts said profit-taking eroded some of the stock market's early gains, and some observers warned the recent rally had not been broad-based enough to be sustained The skeptics note that short-term interest rates near 9 percent are making <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> issues such as one-year bills attractive compared with the uncertain yields on stocks.
