<HEAD>Prosecutors Say Probe Continues, Victims Unlikely to Get Money Back</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By GEORGE GARTIES</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A federal investigation of fraud at the <ORGANIZATION> ZZZZ </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Best </ORGANIZATION> rug shampooing company continues despite the conviction of owner <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> <PERSON> Minkow </PERSON> and his accountant, the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> attorney said Tuesday. Investors in the company and other victims of its scams are unlikely to get back any of the $ 65 million to $ 70 million that disappeared into the firm, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Bonner </PERSON> told a news conference. `` It's a sad fact that in many of these fraud cases, there is n't much left when it is all over,'' <PERSON> Bonner </PERSON> said `` Certainly much of it was dissipated on the lifestyle that Mr. <PERSON> Minkow </PERSON> led.'' <PERSON> Minkow </PERSON>, 22, became familiar to millions of people through appearances in television ads and talk shows, portraying himself to the public and the investment community as a teen-age supersalesman whose thriving company began in his parents' garage in the <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Fernando </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>. He was convicted last week of 57 counts of conspiracy, securities fraud, mail fraud and credit card fraud. Jurors rejected his defense that Mafia figures had forced him to swindle investors by falsely claiming his company was making a fortune restoring fire - and water-damaged buildings <PERSON> Minkow </PERSON>'s accountant, <PERSON> Norman </PERSON> <PERSON> Rothberg </PERSON>, 52, was convicted Monday of taking a bribe from <PERSON> Minkow </PERSON> to cover up the fraud. Ten others connected with ZZZZ Best have pleaded guilty to various charges since the firm collapsed in July 1987. <PERSON> Bonner </PERSON> said his office, the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> were following leads that surfaced at